This paper is about using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for data augmentation in medical imaging, specifically for improving the performance of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) in classification, object detection, and segmentation tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
